""" This is a flask cheat sheet for everyday referance """

##### Installation ####

step 1: create a virtual environment & activate
    --> see virtual environment coding referances if necessary

step 2: install flask in the virtual environment using pip/pip3
    --> pip3 install flask
      --> check flask version = python3 -c "import flask; print(flask.__version__)"

step 3: create a basic application and check if flask working
    --> 
        from flask import Flask

        app = Flask(__name__)

        @app.route('/')
        def hello():
            return 'Hello, World!'

        --> then run it in debug mode following these command
            Â¬ flask --app hello(app_name) run 
            
            ##########****** DEBUG MODE ON BY DEFAULT!!!******##########
